<article class="node help" id="content">
  <header class="node-head">
    <div class="node-title-line">
      <h1 class="node-title">Help</h1>
      <span class="node-type">about</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="layers">
    <section class="layer">
      <p><strong>{{ site.title }}</strong> is an instance of <strong>{{ site.system_name }}</strong> —
      knowledge structured as a navigable graph of concepts instead of a document you scroll.</p>

      <p>Every concept is a <em>node</em>. Every node has <em>depth layers</em>:
      the name, the definition, the usage, the relationships, the theory.
      Dial in as deep as you need. Stop when understanding clicks.</p>

      <h2>The keys</h2>
      <ul class="key-list">
        <li><kbd>&minus;</kbd> — dial down: deeper into this concept</li>
        <li><kbd>+</kbd> — dial up: back toward the surface</li>
        <li><kbd>&darr;</kbd> — onward: where this concept leads</li>
        <li><kbd>&uarr;</kbd> — back along your path, to the depth you left</li>
        <li><kbd>&rarr;</kbd> — branch: a lateral detour</li>
        <li><kbd>&crarr;</kbd> — return from a branch to exactly where you left</li>
        {% if site.chains -%}
        <li><kbd>[</kbd> — chain: the previous step in the sequence</li>
        <li><kbd>]</kbd> — chain: the next step</li>
        {%- endif %}
        <li><kbd>/</kbd> — search everything</li>
        <li><kbd>?</kbd> — this screen</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The ideas</h2>
      <p>Your path is always visible. Branches return in one keypress.
      <strong>Getting lost is not possible.</strong></p>
      <p>The question box maps what you're wondering to the right node at the right
      depth. The AI is the receptionist, not the doctor — it walks you to the room
      and leaves.</p>

      <p class="help-colophon">Content and system by {{ site.author }} ·
      <a href="{{ site.repo }}">source</a> · {{ site.tagline }} ·
      no tracking, no cookies, no external requests, obviously.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</article>
